//
// Design (what changed from the 0.898 frontier):
//   * The FP64 range reduction (x - 2π*rint(x/2π) in double) is replaced with
//     fp32 Cody-Waite two-constant reduction:
//       k = nearbyintf(x * INV_2PI)
//       r = fmaf(-k, TWOPI_HI, x) - k * TWOPI_LO
//     This avoids the slow FP64 divide (FP64 vector is only ~37 TF on B200),
//     cutting the per-thread latency chain from ~4 FP64 ops to ~4 FP32 ops.
//     Accurate to ~1e-5 for |x| < 1e5 (freqs ≤ seq_len_max = 4096).
//   * Everything else is unchanged from the frontier: 2 freqs/thread via
//     float2 load, packed __nv_bfloat162 stores to both output halves,
//     natural grid = cdiv(n_pairs, 256), no over-spreading.

